cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with secure communication in a bidirectional relay, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves designing explicit strategies, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
